ur fiscal house have declined significantly thanks in large part to a substantial tax increase  the cbo still forecasts deficits into the foreseeable future which is not good or sustainable  in effect our politicians have borrowed some time to make some tough decisions  if they elect to go the easy route of increased taxes again to solve the problem this could spell trouble  a mix of controllingconstrainingcutting entitlements will be needed in our opinion one lesson from the greek drama of the last few weeks… debt works until it doesn’t subscribe to landmark financial advisorskeep up to date on our latest thoughts—subscribe below share thisclick to email this to a friend opens in new windowclick to print opens in new windowclick to share on facebook opens in new windowclick to share on twitter opens in new windowclick to share on linkedin opens in new windowclick to share on google opens in new window leave a comment cancel reply commentname  email  website notify me of followup comments by email notify me of new posts by email subscribe to blog via email enter your email address to subscribe to this blog and receive notifications of new posts by email email address most recent posts hackproof your amazon account november   the most important question in retirement planning october   politics take center stage september   summer planning tip july   the employment challenge june   the future of taxes march   will stocks decline further answer watch the economy september   federal govt status july   brace for the media barrage june   search subscribe  connectkeep up to date on our newsletters—subscribe below categoriescategories select category banks behavioral finance books charitable giving debt economy employment energy estate planning federal reserve financial planning gas government health care interest rates investment planning oil philosophy politics precious metals retirement planning stock market tax planning taxes technology tuition uncategorized world even